As Kim wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/14/2004 at 21:50:45 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>How many different ways can six children line up for a class photo?  
>(I am in a college-level critical thinking class) 
>
>[Difficulty]
>I just am having trouble seeing all the possibilities without 
>repeating a child.
>
>[Thoughts]
>If I understand correctly, I do this like this:
>6 x 5 x 4 x 3 x 2 x 1 = 720
>Am I thinking along the right lines?

You're right.  The first kid can be any of the 6.  Once you've
chosen him or her, there are 5 ways to fill the next slot, for
a total of 6x5 ways to fill the first two.  For each of those 6x5
ways, there are 4 kids available to fill the third slot, and so on.


